			<td class="subhead">Scott&nbsp;Wilkinson</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td><b>Video Editor,&nbsp;<i>The Perfect Vision</i></b></td>
		</tr>
		
		
		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Wilkinson_Scott.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;Scott Wilkinson has enjoyed 20 years as an author and editor in the home theater arena. He currently serves as video editor of <I>The Perfect Vision</I> magazine, writing features, columns, and reviews of HDTVs and other video products at Grayscale Studio, TPV’s video-testing lab in Burbank, California. He can also be heard each Saturday morning discussing home theater on Leo Laporte’s nationally syndicated radio talk show, <I>The Tech Guy</I>. Previous positions include writing and editing for <I>Home Theater</I>  and <I>Stereophile Guide to Home Theater</I> magazines, both of which he helped launch, as well as <I>Ultimate A/V, Audio/Video Interiors, Connected</I>, etown.com, and <I>DVD Preview with Leonard Maltin</I>.

As a professional musician, Scott plays many different wind instruments, such as tuba, trombone, didgeridoo, conch-shell trumpet, recorder, ocarina, and various ethnic flutes, and he can be heard on the soundtracks of the movies <I>Gladiator, White Squall</I>, and <I>Mystic India</I> as well as the video games <I>Myst 4</I> and <I>Uncharted</I>. He has also recorded two albums with his avant-garde trio Many Axes and one with his wife, singer-songwriter Joanna Cazden.
</td>
		
		
